1.10	1988_American_League_Championship_Series	1988 American League Championship Series	The 1988 American League Championship Series was a best-of-seven series that pitted the Eastern Division champion Boston Red Sox against the Western Division champion Oakland Athletics. It was the second meeting between the two in ALCS play. The Athletics swept the Series four games to none and would go on to lose to the Los Angeles Dodgers in the 1988 World Series.	
